<TITLE> Hamid now faces extortion charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Naogaon, Mar 22 (bdnews24.com) Former deputy speaker Akhtar Hamid Siddiqui was facing two counts of extortion Sunday, a day after he was detained for "seditious statements". Shamima Yasmin, head teacher of Bagdob secondary school, and Ferdous Alam, a local LGED contractor, filed the cases with Mahadevpur thana. Two police officers, who had served as officers-in-charge of Badalgachhi thana, also lodged separate complaints with local police, alleging extortion and physical assault. Yasmin alleged the former deputy speaker took Tk 1.7 lakh promising to enlist her school for MPO facility, but did not deliver on his promise. Ferdous Alam alleged that, while pursuing construction contracts with various government departments, he had to pay Siddiqui Tk 8 lakh in several instalments. Rabindranath Biswas, a former Badalgachhi OC, alleged the former deputy speaker assaulted him and got him transferred when he failed to pay Siddiqui Tk 4 lakh. Yasin Ali, another former Badalgachhi OC, he suffered physical assault when did not to pay Tk 1 lakh. b
